<subSubSection id="C32C6559FAB8FF76CBFFBFBAFEBFFE07" lastPageId="222" lastPageNumber="223" pageId="221" pageNumber="222" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8936D2FAB8FF76CBFFBFBAFEBFFE07" blockId="221.[151,1436,1697,2010]" lastBlockId="222.[151,1437,151,896]" lastPageId="222" lastPageNumber="223" pageId="221" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FAB8FF75CBFFBFBAFE72F910" bold="true" box="[199,410,1697,1722]" pageId="221" pageNumber="222">
Description. 
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FAB8FF75CA67BFBAFE72F910" bold="true" box="[351,410,1697,1722]" italics="true" pageId="221" pageNumber="222">Shell</emphasis>
</emphasis>
very small (to 
<quantity id="4CCE9B37FAB8FF75C97DBFBAFD73F913" box="[581,667,1697,1721]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.3" pageId="221" pageNumber="222" unit="mm" value="9.3">9.3 mm</quantity>
in total length), fusiform, translucent, glossy-smooth, with up to 
<number id="3DFE24F5FAB8FF75CE41BFBAFA6EF913" box="[1401,1414,1697,1721]" pageId="221" pageNumber="222" value="9.0">9</number>
¼ smooth convex whorls with impressed sutures, the last approximately 
<number id="3DFE24F5FAB8FF75C884BFDEFC30F977" box="[956,984,1733,1757]" pageId="221" pageNumber="222" value="56.0">56</number>
% of the total length; sculpture of axial ribs; aperture narrowly oval, only slightly wider at its widest than anterior canal. 
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FAB8FF75CF14BFF2FB5AF8A8" bold="true" box="[1068,1202,1769,1794]" italics="true" pageId="221" pageNumber="222">Protoconch</emphasis>
